-- Mike Catt Named Attacking Skills Coach for England Rugby Team
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-09-07T18:36:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-07/mike-catt-named-attacking-skills-coach-for-england-rugby-team.html
Mike Catt was named the England
rugby team’s attacking skills coach, the Rugby Football Union
said in a statement.  Catt joins Graham Rowntree and Andy Farrell on the senior
staff of coach  Stuart Lancaster . The 40-year-old was part of
Lancaster’s staff for England’s tour of South Africa this
summer.  The South African-born Catt helped England win the 2003
World Cup during his 75 appearances with the national team.  England will host Fiji, Australia, South Africa and world
champion  New Zealand  during its autumn Test series from Nov. 10
to Dec. 1  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
